#
# why error AttributeError: addinfourl instance has no attribute '__exit__' in urllib, urllib2 in Python2.7
#
1) >>> with urllib.urlopen(url2) as u:
...     print(u2.read())
... 
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<stdin>", line 1, in <module>
AttributeError: addinfourl instance has no attribute '__exit__'

Root cause:
  in Python 2.7, with urllib.urlopen(...) is not supported.
  and urllib, urllib2 has no readall() function, use read().
  
Fix:
  u1 = urllib2.urlopen(url1)
  print(u1.read())
  
  u2 = urllib.urlopen(url2)
  for line in u2:
    print(line.read())
    
    
